data.enText: to arrange for yourself or for sb else to officially join a course, school, etc.

data.chText: 你必须在八月底前注册。
data.enText: You need to enrol before the end of August.

data.chText: 中心将很快为新课程的招生做好准备。
data.enText: The centre will soon be ready to enrol candidates for the new programme.

ex.enText: He enlisted at the age of 18.
He was enlisted into the navy.

ex.chText: 她在一家职业介绍所登记谋求秘书职位。
ex.enText: She enrolled with an employment agency for a secretarial job.

ex.chText: 学院将于8月份招收新生。
ex.enText: The college will enrol new students in August.

synonyms.bx: 通常指吸收新成员、招收新生、登记学习某一课程等。

ex.chText: 我的公司难以招募到素质好的职员。
ex.enText: My company is having difficulties in recruiting well-qualified staff.

ex.chText: 他的工作是为陆军募兵。
ex.enText: His job is to recruit for the army.

synonyms.bx: 多指招募新员工、新成员、新兵等。

tr: register formally as a participant or member
example: The party recruited many new members

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 enroll

value.def: If you enrol or are enrolled at an institution or on a course, you officially join it and pay a fee for it.

example.ex: Cherny was enrolled at the University in 1945...
example.tran: 彻尼1945年在该大学登记入学。

example.ex: She enrolled on a local Women Into Management course...
example.tran: 她注册学习当地的“女性参与管理”课程。

example.ex: At 33 he enrolled in a glass-making degree course at London's Royal College of Art...
example.tran: 33岁时，他在伦敦皇家艺术学院注册学习玻璃制作学位课程。

example.ex: I thought I'd enrol you with an art group at the school.
example.tran: 我想我会吸收你参加学校的一个艺术团。

value.tran: 招收（成员）；招（生）登记入学;注册（课程）
